                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 774/764.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Beaupré</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Hague</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-07-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 19, 1910</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Mr. Beaupré acknowledges department’s cablegram of July 14, and says that
                    September 15 will be satisfactory to the Government of the Netherlands for
                    meeting of opium conference. Mr. Beaupré adds that the minister for foreign
                    affairs desires to be informed at once what Governments have adhered to the
                    principle of the calling of the conference so that invitations may be
                    issued.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
